Correct loom files cell ID¶

In [6]:
def loom_cellid(meta_row):
    
    """Removes velocyto pattern from cell ids if present"""
    
    # Open connection to loom file 
    ds = lp.connect(meta_row['sample_path'] + '/velocyto.loom')
    
    # Change velocyto cell id to original id 
    cell_id = ds.ca['CellID'] # np.array 
    cell_id = pd.Series(cell_id)
    
    # Remove velocyto extension and add sample cell id idx 
    if bool(re.search('x', cell_id[0])): 

        cell_id = cell_id.str.split(':').str.get(1) # Cut after file name appendix
        cell_id = cell_id.str.split('x').str.get(0) # Remove tailing x
        cell_id = cell_id + "-1_" + str(meta_row['cell_id_idx']) # cell id idx from seurat merge
        ds.ca['CellID'] = np.array(cell_id) # replace cellid 
        
    else:
        
        print(meta_row['sample_path'] + ' no velocyto cell id detected. Leaving untouched')
    
    # Close loom connection 
    ds.close()
    
meta.apply(loom_cellid, axis=1)

Combine and annotate velocyto loom files or import pre-computed file¶

The cell ids are the same between seurat and velocyto loom files. However, velocyto carries over all genes (var) from the reference gtf thereby introducing many zero count genes. When intersecting with seurat and velocyto anndata objects those get removed.

In [7]:
if combine_loom: 
    # Combine velocyto loom files 
    lp.combine(list(meta['sample_path'] + '/velocyto.loom'), 'data/loom_object/loom_velocyto.loom')
    # Import velocyto loom as anndata
    adata_velocyto = scv.read_loom('data/loom_object/loom_velocyto.loom')
    # Import Seurat loom as anndata
    adata_seurat = scv.read_loom('data/loom_object/loom_qc.loom')
    # Merge velocyto with seurat anndata
    adata = scv.utils.merge(adata_seurat, adata_velocyto)
    # Save velocyto adata as loom file 
    adata.write_loom('data/loom_object/loom_velocyto.loom', write_obsm_varm=False) 

else: 
    adata = scv.read_loom('data/loom_object/loom_velocyto.loom')
